Check the status: To verify if Jenkins is running or to troubleshoot issues, use:
bash
sudo systemctl status jenkins
This command provides details such as whether the service is active, the main process ID, and recent log entries.
Stop the service: To manually stop Jenkins, run:
bash
sudo systemctl stop jenkins
Restart the service: This command stops and then starts Jenkins in a single step:
bash
sudo systemctl restart jenkins
Enable auto-start on boot: To ensure Jenkins starts automatically when the system boots, use:
bash
sudo systemctl enable jenkins
